#, no-wrap
msgid "FreeBSD Code of Conduct Reporting Instructions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:11
msgid ""
"If you believe someone is violating the link:../code-of-conduct[code of "
"conduct] we ask that you report it to the FreeBSD Code of Conduct Committee "
"by emailing conduct@freebsd.org."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:13
msgid ""
"All reports will be kept confidential whenever possible. We strive to "
"protect the identity and safety of reporters. In some cases we may need to "
"make a public statement of some form, in which case we will use the minimum "
"of details and identifying information necessary to protect our "
"community. In rare cases, we may need to identify some of the people "
"involved to comply with the law or protect other potential victims. In these "
"cases, we will consult with the reporter to find out what their wishes are "
"and take them into account in our final decision. In all cases, we will not "
"directly or indirectly identify reporters without their consent unless we "
"see no other option."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:15
msgid ""
"If you believe anyone is in physical danger, please notify appropriate law "
"enforcement first."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:17
msgid "In your report please include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:19
msgid ""
"Your name and contact info (so we can get in touch with you if we need to "
"follow up)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:20
msgid ""
"Names (real, nicknames, and/or pseudonyms) of any individuals involved. If "
"there were other witnesses besides you, please try to include them as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:21
msgid "When and where the incident occurred. Please be as specific as possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:22
msgid ""
"Your account of what occurred. If there is a publicly available record "
"(e.g. a mailing list archive, tweet, or a public IRC logger) please include "
"a link and/or screen shots."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:23
msgid "Any extra context you believe relevant for the incident."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:24
msgid "If you believe this incident is ongoing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:25
msgid "Any other information you believe we should have."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "What happens after you file a report?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:29
msgid ""
"You will receive an email from the FreeBSD Code of Conduct Committee "
"acknowledging receipt of your report within 48 hours."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:31
msgid ""
"The committee will meet as quickly as possible to review the incident and "
"determine:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:33
msgid ""
"Whether an investigation is needed, including interviewing additional "
"parties or witnesses;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:34
msgid "What appears to have happened and;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:35
msgid "Whether the behavior constitutes a Code of Conduct violation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:37
msgid ""
"If a member of the FreeBSD Code of Conduct Committee is one of the "
"individuals included in the report they will recuse themselves from handling "
"the report."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:39
msgid ""
"Once the working group has a complete account of the events they will make a "
"decision as to how to respond. Actions taken may include:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:41
msgid "Nothing (for example, if we determine that no violation occurred)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:42
msgid ""
"If determined to be solely technical in nature or if it falls outside the "
"scope of the Code of Conduct, forwarding the incident to the FreeBSD Core "
"Team"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:43
msgid "A private reprimand from the working group to the individual(s) involved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:44
msgid "A public reprimand."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:45
msgid ""
"An imposed vacation from FreeBSD Project controlled spaces (e.g. asking "
"someone to \"take a week off\" from a mailing list or IRC)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:46
msgid ""
"A permanent or temporary ban from some or all FreeBSD Project controlled "
"spaces (events, meetings, mailing lists, IRC, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:47
msgid "A request for a public or private apology."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:48
msgid "A request to engage in mediation and/or an accountability plan."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:50
msgid ""
"We will do our best to respond within one week to the person who filed the "
"report with either a resolution or an explanation of why the situation is "
"not yet resolved."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:52
msgid ""
"Once we have determined our final action, we will contact the original "
"reporter to let them know what action (if any) we will be taking. We will "
"take into account feedback from the reporter on the appropriateness of our "
"response, but we do not guarantee we will act on it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:54
msgid ""
"Finally, the committee will make a report on the situation to the FreeBSD "
"Core Team. The Core Team may choose to issue a public report of the "
"incident."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:55
#, no-wrap
msgid "Appeals"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: content/en/internal/conduct-reporting.adoc:57
msgid ""
"Only permanent resolutions (such as bans) may be appealed. To appeal a "
"decision of the CoC Committee, contact the FreeBSD Core Team at "
"core@freebsd.org with your appeal and the Core Team will review the case."
msgstr ""
